//Object initialization can be done in 3 ways

------

1. using reference variable:

//Animal.java

class Animal{

    String color;
    int age;
    public static void main(String[] args){
    
    Animal buzo = new Animal();
    buzo.color = "black";    //initializing object using dot operator i.e reference variable
    buzo.age = 10;
    System.out.print("Buzo color : " + buzo.color + " Buzo age : " + buzo.age);
    }
}    

o/p:
Buzo color : black Buzo age : 10

------

2. using method:

//Animal.java

class Animal{

    String color; 
    int age;
    public void initObj(String a, int b){
        color = a;
        age = b; 
    }
    public void display(){
        System.out.print("Buzo color : " + color + "Buzo age : " + age);
    }
    
    public static void main(String[] args){
    Animal buzo = new Animal();
    buzo.initObj("black",10);
    buzo.display();
    }
} 

o/p:
Buzo color : black Buzo age : 10

------

